The only downside to the hotel was the cost of parking, but apparently that is pretty much standard in Chicago.	I eventually made it to the junior suite but was amazed at the smallness of the room which is really saying something coming from the UK and the standard size of hotel room here.	I am a big fan a larger, chain hotels but overall, I can recommend Sutton Place Chicago.	This year it was sub-standard.	The rooms were cleaned to a high standard.	The size of the hotel is great, large enough but seems intimate.	The room at the hotel was large with a king size bed.